    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Walkways, concentric with the rows of seats, between the upper and lower seating tiers in a Roman theater.  For similar features in Greek theaters, use "diazomata."</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Doorgangen tussen hoger en lager gelegen rijen zitplaatsen in Romeinse theaters. Gebruik 'diazomata' voor soortgelijke doorgangen in Griekse theaters.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052396/Koch, Europese bouwstijlen (1988)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>羅馬劇院中，位於梯形座位上下層之間，與各排座位呈同心狀的走道。希臘劇院中此類構造則稱為「走道(diazomata)」。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Konzentrisch zu den Sitzreihen verlaufender Umgang in einem römischen Theater zwischen den oberen und unteren Zuschauerreihen. Ähnliche Gänge in griechischen Theatern werden "Diazomata" genannt.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
